Data

First, we load in the ’18 data. There are some big issues with the data (multiple zscores are NA, about half of the data has no information for items), so some serious cleanup is warranted.

df.english <- read.delim("Eng18.txt") 


df.english <- df.english %>% 
  drop_na() %>%
  filter(Age != "18. This is me, Alex.") %>% # Remove NAs and other weird things
  select(participant, condition, response, zscore, list, stimuli2, stimuli3) %>%
  mutate(filler=ifelse(grepl("f", condition, fixed=TRUE), 1, 0)) %>% # Binary coding for filler/not filler
  rename("itemN"=stimuli2, "itemText" = stimuli3)

df.english$condition   <- factor(df.english$condition)
df.english$participant <- factor(df.english$participant)
df.english$list        <- factor(df.english$list)
df.english$itemN       <- factor(df.english$itemN)

Here we will be analyzing the D-linking experiment only, so we’ll create a couple of filtered dataframes. One for the D-linking data:

# Get D-link items
dlink.conditions <- c("ShortBare", "ShortD", "ShortDOf", "LongBare", "LongD", "LongDOf")
df.english.dlink <- df.english %>% filter(condition %in% dlink.conditions)

# Reorder levels
df.english.dlink$condition <- factor(df.english.dlink$condition, levels = c("ShortBare", "ShortD", "ShortDOf", "LongBare", "LongD", "LongDOf"))

# Summary
df.english.dlink %>% group_by(condition) %>% summarize(count=n(), mean=mean(zscore), sd=sd(zscore), se=sd / sqrt(count)) %>% ungroup()

In order to do a proper 2x3, the data must be recoded, so we do that here.

df.english.dlink <- df.english.dlink %>% 
  mutate(distance=ifelse(
    condition=="ShortBare" | condition == "ShortD" | condition=="ShortDOf", "Short", "Long"), 
    dlink=ifelse(
      condition=="ShortBare" | condition=="LongBare", "Bare", 
      ifelse(condition=="ShortD" | condition=="LongD", "D", "DOf")
      ),
    dlinkBin=ifelse(
      condition=="ShortBare" | condition=="LongBare", "Bare", "DLink"
      )
    )

# Create factors
df.english.dlink$distance    <- factor(df.english.dlink$distance, levels=c("Short", "Long"))
df.english.dlink$dlink       <- factor(df.english.dlink$dlink, levels=c("Bare", "D", "DOf"))
df.english.dlink$dlinkBin    <- factor(df.english.dlink$dlinkBin, levels=c("Bare", "DLink"))

# Summaries
df.english.dlink %>% group_by(distance, dlink) %>% summarize(count=n(), mean=mean(zscore), sd=sd(zscore), se=sd / sqrt(count)) %>% ungroup()

Mixed-effects model

Finally, we fit a linear mixed-effects regression. But I’m not actually sure what the plan was for data analysis, so it probably needs tweaking. At any rate, there are main effects of Dlinking and distance, but they’re in the wrong direction…

# Define contrasts
contrasts(df.english.dlink$distance) <- cbind(c(-1, 1))
contrasts(df.english.dlink$dlink)    <- cbind(c(1, -1, 0), c(1, 1, -2))

# Alternative coding (unused)
#df.english.dlink <- df.english.dlink %>% 
#  mutate(dlinkCont = ifelse(dlink=="Bare",-1,ifelse(dlink=="D", 0, 1)), 
#         distCont = ifelse(distance=="Short", -1, 1))

# Linear mixed-effects
# Note: Currently won't converge with by-item intercepts

out.lmer <- lmer(zscore ~ distance*dlink + (1 | participant) + (1 | list), data=df.english.dlink)
summary(out.lmer)
